racket%2Fprivate%2Fbase..rkt%29._for%2Fsum%29%29\">for/sum</a></span> to add up the partial derivatives. Instead, we use <span class=\"RktSym\"><a class=\"RktStxLink Sq\" data-pltdoc=\"x\" href=\"https://docs.racket-lang.org/reference/for.html#%28form._%28%28lib._racket%2Fprivate%2Fbase..rkt%29._for%2Ffold%29%29\">for/fold</a></span>, which accumulates the <span class=\"RktSym\">sum</span> variable as we loop over the inputs.</p>\n\n<p>Here is an example of using <span class=\"RktSym\"><a class=\"RktStxLink Sq\" data-pltdoc=\"x\" href=\"https://docs.racket-lang.org/reference/for.html#%28form._%28%28lib._racket%2Fprivate%2Fbase..rkt%29._for%2Ffold%29%29\">for/fold</a></span>:</p>\n\n<div class=\"SCodeFlow\">\n <table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"RktBlk\">\n  <tbody>\n   <tr>\n    <td><span class=\"stt\">&gt; </span><span class=\"RktPn\">(</span><span class=\"RktSym\"><a class=\"RktStxLink Sq\" data-pltdoc=\"x\" href=\"https://docs.racket-lang.org/reference/define.html#%28form._%28%28lib._racket%2Fprivate%2Fbase..rkt%29._define%29%29\">define</a></span><span class=\"hspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"RktSym\">words</span><span class=\"hspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"RktPn\">(</span><span class=\"RktSym\"><a class=\"RktValLink Sq\" data-pltdoc=\"x\" href=\"https://docs.racket-lang.org/reference/pairs.html#%28def._%28%28quote._~23~25kernel%29._list%29%29\">list</a></span><span class=\"hspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"RktVal\">\"My \"</span><span class=\"hspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"RktVal\">\"name \"</span><span class=\"hspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"RktVal\">\"is \"</span><span class=\"hspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"RktVal\">\"Mike.\"</span><span class=\"RktPn\">)</span><span class=\"RktPn\">)</span></td></tr>\n   <tr>\n    <td>\n     <table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"RktBlk\">\n      <tbody>\n       <tr>\n        <td><span class=\"stt\">&gt; </span><span class=\"RktPn\">(</span><span class=\"RktSym\"><a class=\"